How to Fix a Football Match
Football fever has gripped the globe with all the action from the World Cup in Brazil; however it seems there is a darker side to the game which Morland Sanders finds out tonight in this episode of Dispatches. He goes undercover to investigate allegations of match-fixing around the globe, and asking if fans can even trust what they're watching. Hard to believe that much corruption could exist in the sport that's loved by so many so let's hope these investigations don't produce too many sketchy results.
